
.TH HOARE 1 "${DATE}" "hoare ${HOARE_VERSION_STRING}" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
hoare \- the hoare compiler
.SH SYNOPSIS
hoare [OPTION]... [FILE]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hoare
is a compiler for the language described in Sir Tony Hoare's paper
"Communicating Sequential Processes". Depending on the options being passed,
it can behave as either a compiler or an interpreter.
.SH OPTIONS
.IP "\fB\-h, \-\-help\fR" 4
.IX Item "--help"
Display available options.
.IP "\fB\-S\fR" 4
.IX Item "-S"
Emit the LLVM representation assembler. It emits the representation into a new
file with the .ll extension. This file can then be compiled with clang in order
to produce a platform-dependent binary.
.IP "\fB\-v, \-\-version\fR" 4
.IX Item "--version"
Show the current version.
.SH BUGS
To report bugs, please visit <https://github.com/mssola/hoare/issues>.
